    "title" : "json invalid format to valid format",
    "body" : "<p>I have invalid json coming from rest api. How can we make it valid json.</p>\n<p><strong>Actual Output:</strong></p>\n<pre><code>{&quot;results&quot; : {\n    &quot;Name&quot; : &quot;xxxx, &quot;yyyy&quot;&quot;,\n    &quot;Role&quot; : &quot;developer&quot;,\n    &quot;Address&quot; : &quot;&quot;\n}}\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Expected Output:</strong></p>\n<pre><code>{&quot;results&quot; : {\n    &quot;Name&quot; : &quot;xxxx, 'yyyy'&quot;,\n    &quot;Role&quot; : &quot;developer&quot;,\n    &quot;Address&quot; : &quot;&quot;\n}}\n</code></pre>\n<p>How can we remove double quotes inside the Name value and replace single quotes?</p>\n<p>Tried below options:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><p>First converting from json string to json object\nBut cannot convert as the json is invalid, cannot read it.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><code>String.replaceall()</code> but it replaces other values also like address.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n",
